    "prompt": "Repeat with compass directions NW, NE, SW, SE. ",
    "source_code": "\r\n# Given a point with integer coordinates (x, y) and a compass direction NW, NE, SW, SE, \r\n# print the neighboring lattice point in the given direction. A lattice is a structure\r\n# in which all points are equidistant away from one another, in this case, each is \r\n# point is 1 unit away in either the x or y direction. Print the new point in the \r\n# format (x, y).\r\n\r\nx = 0 \ny = 0 \ndirection = 'NW' \n\r\n# Your code here...\n"
